"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541042","Department of Health","false","2016-09-05","<p>I understand that the British Liver Trust is working in partnership with the Royal College of General Practitioners on a three year programme to make liver disease a clinical priority for primary care. This is aimed at improving awareness and understanding of liver disease as well as treatment amongst those working in primary care.</p><p> </p><p>Public Health England is currently developing a framework to tackle liver disease. This will include the action that needs to be taken across the health and care system, including in primary care, to prevent and better manage liver disease.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","43645","2016-09-05T08:53:18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541042/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541042/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541042/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-07-20","Liver Diseases: Health Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department is taking to increase awareness of liver disease in the (a) general population and (b) NHS.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","43644"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541043","Department of Health","false","2016-09-05","<p>I understand that the British Liver Trust is working in partnership with the Royal College of General Practitioners on a three year programme to make liver disease a clinical priority for primary care. This is aimed at improving awareness and understanding of liver disease as well as treatment amongst those working in primary care.</p><p> </p><p>Public Health England is currently developing a framework to tackle liver disease. This will include the action that needs to be taken across the health and care system, including in primary care, to prevent and better manage liver disease.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","43644","2016-09-05T08:53:18.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541043/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541043/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541043/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-07-20","Liver Diseases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department is taking to improve (a) expertise and (b) facilities in primary care to strengthen (i) detection of early liver disease and (ii) treatment for liver disease.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","43645"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541044","Department of Health","false","2016-09-05","<p>Public Health England (PHE) has developed and publishes liver disease profiles for all local authorities in England. The profiles provide support to local areas to understand liver disease and its risk factors in their area. They present key local statistics and highlight questions to ask locally about current action to prevent liver disease.</p><p> </p><p>The Local Authority Liver Disease Profiles demonstrate geographical variation in the main risk factors: alcohol, obesity, hepatitis B and C which explain some of the regional and local authority variations in outcome. Experts at PHE in these three areas regularly review these statistics and the evidence for intervention. The profiles demonstrate that there are widespread opportunities to reduce mortality from liver disease prevention.</p><p> </p><p>PHE is also updating the 2013 NHS Atlas of Variation in Healthcare for People with Liver Disease highlighting variations in risk factors, health services and outcomes.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-09-05T08:52:35.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541044/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541044/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541044/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-07-20","Liver Diseases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment has been made of the causes of regional variation in liver disease outcomes in England.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","43646"
